A security officer guarding a funeral parlour was gunned down on Friday morning, at a business premises next to Bridge City Shopping centre in KwaMashu. Netcare 911 and SAPS were on scene. According to Shawn Herbst of Netcare 911, they arrived to find an adult man lying face down in a pool of blood. “He was surrounded by at least 12 high calibre bullet casings. The patient was assessed but showed no signs of life and was declared dead on the scene,” said Herbst. He added that the circumstances leading up to the shooting will be investigated by the KwaMashu SAPS.